          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1667321836206-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>salmon & saag aloo-style fishcakes </strong>to one side of a<strong> baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two), drizzle with <strong>olive oil</strong> and put in the oven for 15-20 min or until golden</p><p>Trim your <strong>green beans</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> trimmed green beans</strong> to a large piece of <strong>tin foil </strong>with the <strong>remaining chopped ginger</strong> and <strong>garlic</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>water</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1667322295050-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1667322295050-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1667322295050-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1667322295050-x1000.jpg",
